In 1947, a high-altitude balloon from Project Mogul crashed in Roswell, New Mexico. The official statement from the 509th Bombardment Group at Roswell Army Air Field stated they had “come into possession of a Flying Saucer.”

Spikes in UFO sightings align with current events

UFO sightings by year, according to the National UFO Reporting Center, June 2023.

The movie Apollo 13 was released in 1995, making a gross profit of $172,036,360. Just one year later, Independence Day was released bringing in $817.4 million.

The 2010s saw a peak with over 63,000 sightings. Between 2012 - 2015, the average sightings were sitting at just under 8,000/year. Numbers didn’t reach that height again until 2020 when the pandemic gave people plenty of time to stare out windows.
